    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_7_11967-12039",
      "chapterUid": 7,
      "range": "11967-12039",
      "markText": "他清楚地知道，自由越大，秩序越弱。辩证地来看，过度的自由，最终会导致失去自由。汉密尔顿一生的任务就是要尽力解决这一矛盾，以平衡自由与秩序的关系。",
      "totalCount": 576,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=7&rangeStart=11967&rangeEnd=12039",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=7&rangeStart=11967&rangeEnd=12039"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_5_12851-12949",
      "chapterUid": 5,
      "range": "12851-12949",
      "markText": "汉密尔顿并没有意识到，这封信让他摆脱了贫困。事实证明，这场自然灾害拯救了汉密尔顿。就连圣·克罗伊岛的总督也开始打听起作者的身份了，当地的商人们决定凑一笔钱把这个前途无量的小伙子送到北美去接受教育。",
      "totalCount": 510,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=5&rangeStart=12851&rangeEnd=12949",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=5&rangeStart=12851&rangeEnd=12949"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_7_5304-5378",
      "chapterUid": 7,
      "range": "5304-5378",
      "markText": "美国革命最终能够成功，也正是由于它一直是由一群杰出人物所推动的，而这些人清楚地知道，用来打倒暴政的革命激情如果不加以控制，会变质为巨大的破坏性力量。",
      "totalCount": 432,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=7&rangeStart=5304&rangeEnd=5378",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=7&rangeStart=5304&rangeEnd=5378"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_6_32271-32355",
      "chapterUid": 6,
      "range": "32271-32355",
      "markText": "汉密尔顿的这种尖刻的攻击使得他成为北美最可怕的辩论者，这也让他收获了和朋友一样多的死敌。与富兰克林和杰斐逊不同，汉密尔顿并不擅长用怀柔的策略和委婉机智的语言来征服敌手。",
      "totalCount": 400,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=32271&rangeEnd=32355",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=32271&rangeEnd=32355"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_3_623-711",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "623-711",
      "markText": "在19世纪50年代早期的日子里，当人们走过白宫附近H大街的那一片房子的时候，几乎没有人会想到那位坐在窗边收拾花草的老寡妇，是最后一位尚健在的与美国早年建国的光辉岁月有所瓜葛的人",
      "totalCount": 391,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=623&rangeEnd=711",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=623&rangeEnd=711"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_12_7338-7410",
      "chapterUid": 12,
      "range": "7338-7410",
      "markText": "汉密尔顿越发对纯粹的民主政治感到绝望，对只是迎合大众意愿的政治家感到失望，越来越喜爱受过教育而有教养的，能够启发人们做出他们自己的判断的领导者。",
      "totalCount": 378,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=12&rangeStart=7338&rangeEnd=7410",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=12&rangeStart=7338&rangeEnd=7410"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_4_26043-26126",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "26043-26126",
      "markText": "由于这层关系，汉密尔顿得以从小就认识了奴隶身上的人性，而这给汉密尔顿的思想带来了深刻的影响，后来他便成了美国国父中比较早地认识到奴隶制的丑恶而坚定地主张废奴的人之一。",
      "totalCount": 340,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=26043&rangeEnd=26126",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=26043&rangeEnd=26126"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_10_2153-2217",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "2153-2217",
      "markText": "虽然那些风情万种、率性而为的开放女子总是让他着迷，但是当他选择妻子的时候，他看重的却是那种通情达理、可靠而有一点迷人的良家女子。",
      "totalCount": 340,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2153&rangeEnd=2217",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=2153&rangeEnd=2217"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_9_8520-8584",
      "chapterUid": 9,
      "range": "8520-8584",
      "markText": "读了汉密尔顿的这本笔记本，我们就不会奇怪为什么他会成为第一流的宪法专家、无人可以超越的财政部长和美国第一起著名性丑闻的男主角了。",
      "totalCount": 336,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=9&rangeStart=8520&rangeEnd=8584",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=9&rangeStart=8520&rangeEnd=8584"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_4_1694-1778",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "1694-1778",
      "markText": "由于当地的加勒比人和欧洲人并不能适应在闷热的甘蔗园里的繁重工作，于是，成千上万的非洲黑人被从西非的那些奴隶贸易据点整船整船地运到加勒比来开发尼维斯岛和邻近岛屿的种植园。",
      "totalCount": 330,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=1694&rangeEnd=1778",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=1694&rangeEnd=1778"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_6_11204-11281",
      "chapterUid": 6,
      "range": "11204-11281",
      "markText": "人们不难发现汉密尔顿将自己的生活弄得紧张兮兮，这或许是因为他在一生中都长期对于自己在起跑线上就落后于别人而耿耿于怀，因此急不可耐地希望能够迎头赶上的缘故。",
      "totalCount": 330,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=11204&rangeEnd=11281",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=11204&rangeEnd=11281"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_5_10402-10447",
      "chapterUid": 5,
      "range": "10402-10447",
      "markText": "你野心勃勃地想要超越自己，总想竭力在自己做的每一件事上尽善尽美，现在的你，已经非常脆弱了。",
      "totalCount": 324,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=5&rangeStart=10402&rangeEnd=10447",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=5&rangeStart=10402&rangeEnd=10447"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_4_29097-29175",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "29097-29175",
      "markText": "在母亲死后的一年中，汉密尔顿一直被这场悬而未决的遗产诉讼折磨着，而这段经历或许让他早早看清楚了社会的本质：谁能够将法律玩弄于股掌之间，谁就拥有了真正的权力。",
      "totalCount": 289,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=934609&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=29097&rangeEnd=29175",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/25a320305e42d125a701c29?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=29097&rangeEnd=29175"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "934609_8_6287-6323",
      "chapterUid": 8,
      "range": "6287-6323",
      "markText": "后来华盛顿以花岗岩般的冷静闻名天下，实际上他也曾经是个脾气暴躁的小伙子。",
      "totalCount": 288,
